July 20, 2017
                  
                  
                    /
5g
/ Posted By: rachel.rorke

This weekend marks the final days of a next generation 5G Internet trial in Bristol, England. The trial, called Bristol is Open (BIO, for short) is designed as an internet-enabled scavenger hunt in the central part of Bristol. The trial is open to anyone with an Android device who is interested in testing new technology. Users with Android devices are invited to participate by downloading the app and taking part in a walk-around search for... Read More




